OL,3,CMartyn's Law to receive Royal Assent
OL,4,Cafter campaign by Martyn Hett's mother
OL,6,F"I'm grateful to the Prime Minister
OL,7,Ffor keeping his promise and for the
OL,8,Fwork the Home Office team has
OL,9,Fdelivered to help us get to this
OL,10,Fpoint, but my work is not finished.
OL,12,F"Collaboration is at the core of
OL,13,FMartyn's Law. As we enter the two year
OL,14,Fimplementation period it is essential
OL,15,Fthat everyone plays their part to
OL,16,Fensure that businesses and venues
OL,17,Facross the country can implement the
OL,18,Frequirements to better protect the
OL,19,Fpublic from terrorism."
OL,21,FWhat is Martyn's Law?
